        <para>Once you have clicked the "Create" button, you land in the editor, in the Basic Input Forms, on the first tab, called "Publication."</para>
        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/editor_top_basic.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Clicking on the large Tamboti logo returns you to the search interface, discarding all input you have made, so beware of that!</para>
        <para>If you want to see the Cluster web page, you can do so by clicking the Cluster logo to the right.</para>
        <para>Clicking on "Help" opens the present search interface in another window or tab (depeding on your browser settings), allowing you to work with your
            input and refer to the explanations at the same time.</para>
        <para>To the right, you will a status message, here: "Editing record of type Monograph, with the title Story of My Life, on the Publication tab, to be saved
            in/db/mods/users/editor," detailing which type of record you are inputting ("Monograph"), what its title is, on which tab you are
            editing it, and where it will be saved if you choose to save it. Of course, no title occurs until you have input one. 
            The title will serve to remind you of what you are working with, even when you are not on the form
            where the title information is input.</para>
